This paper is primarily focused on deep reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of temporal abstraction and output representation modeling, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve playing Atari games, which are visual tasks and therefore fall under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the problem of sparse reward signals, which is a common issue in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.CV, cs.RO, and cs.SY.
